{"id": 7818, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "3", "year": "2019", "session": "19N", "subtopic": "a-4-liquid-crystals", "title": "19N.3.SL.TZ0.6", "topic_id": "a", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">A soap solution can form a liquid-crystal state.</span></p>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Describe the arrangement of soap molecules in the nematic liquid crystal phase.</span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">State how liquid crystals are affected by an electric field.</span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">molecules point/align in same direction/orientation<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>molecules have directional order ✔</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">molecules randomly distributed<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>molecules not in a layered arrangement<br/><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br/>molecules do not have positional order ✔</span></p>\n<p><em>NOTE: <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Accept suitable diagram for M1 and M2.</span></em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">molecules align with field ✔</span></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>"}